Preconditions:
The value of `n` must be a positive integer.
The `rides` array must not be null.
The `rides` array must have at least one element.
Each element in the `rides` array must be an array of size 3, representing a ride with start time, end time, and fare.

Postconditions:
The method returns a long value representing the maximum number of dollars that can be earned by picking up the passengers optimally.
The returned value is greater than or equal to zero.
The returned value is the sum of fares from the optimal set of rides.
The optimal set of rides is determined by maximizing the total fare while ensuring that no two rides overlap in time.
If there are no possible rides that can be picked up, the method returns 0.